THIS IS MY LEARNING ABOUT HIDING A SECRET OR HIDING API_KEY AND PASSWORDS IF YOU WANT SECURITY OF YOUR WEBSITE. 

1. INSTALL node.js 
 - JUST GO ON THIS SITE AND COPY THE TERMINAL CODE ON THE DOCUMENTARY.
 - https://nodejs.org/en/download

2. I AM USING LINUX SO IF YOU USING WINDOWS YOU CAN SEARCH IN THE YOUTUBE IF YOU WANT TO LEARN BUT ME I AM USING LINUX
  - OPEN TERMINAL AND CHECK OF YOUR VERSION OF npm AND node.js USING THIS TERMINAL CODE.
  - node -v # Should print "v24.17.0".
  - npm -v # Should print "11.13.0".

3. THEN GO TO YOUR CODE OR VS-CODE AND RUN TERMINAL AND DOWNLOAD THIS
npm install dotenv
npm install express

4. CREATE YOUR FOLDER THAT FOLDER CONTAINS
  - name_server.js
  - .env

5. THEN IN THE .env FILE PUT YOUR API KEY OR PASSWORD 
  - API_KEY=your_secret

6.THEN GO TO THE package.json AND COPY THIS COMMAND

{
  "type": "module",
  "dependencies": {
    "dotenv": "^17.4.2",
    "express": "^4.22.2"
  }
}

7. THEN GO TO THE server.js AND COPY THIS COMMAND FOR RUNNING THE SERVER 

import express from "express";
import dotenv from "dotenv";

dotenv.config();

const app = express();

const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;

app.get("/", (req, res) => {
    res.send("Server is running");
});

app.listen(PORT, () => {
    console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`);
});

8. YOUR DONE YOUR DONE HIDING YOU API_KEY OR YOUR SECRETS 


